# MediClinic Design Language

**Read [DESIGN-LANGUAGE.md](../../DESIGN-LANGUAGE.md) before changing UI.**

## Quick Rules

- **Fonts:** Montserrat (headings) + Inter (body). No script/serif heading fonts.
- **Colors:** Use `:root` tokens in `static/clinic/styles.css`
  - Primary Blue `#3FA9F5` — accents, links, focus (not primary button fill)
  - Gold `#F5B94C` — chips, hover accents (5% of UI)
  - Navy `#1A2D4D` / `#10233F` — header, footer, hero, primary buttons
  - White 60% / Soft Gray `#F4F6F9` 25% surface ratio
- **Layout:** `--page-gutter: clamp(24px, 5vw, 48px)`, max-width 1120px, sticky footer flex column
- **Gallery:** 3 sections per row (`.pairs-grid`); each section has Before + After with multiple titled images
- **i18n:** All UI strings in `clinic/context_processors.py` → `UI_TEXTS` (en + tr)
- **Flags:** SVG in `static/clinic/flags/`, not emoji
- **Modals/lightbox:** Must hide with `[hidden] { display: none !important }`
- **Motion:** Keep starfield + page-glow subtle; hover lift on cards/buttons

When adding new UI, reuse existing classes (`.btn`, `.hero`, `.card`, `.pair-section`, `.form-card`) before creating new ones.
